.TH VULNSCAN-AI 1 "June 2026" "vulnscan-ai @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
vulnscan-ai \- RHEL vulnerability scanner with AI-assisted, approval-gated remediation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vulnscan-ai
[\fIGLOBAL OPTIONS\fR]
.I COMMAND
[\fICOMMAND OPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B vulnscan-ai
scans RHEL-based hosts (RHEL, AlmaLinux, Rocky, CentOS Stream, Fedora) for known
vulnerabilities using the package manager (dnf/RHSA), OpenSCAP/OVAL, and public
CVE feeds (Red Hat Security Data API, NIST NVD). It then uses a large language
model (Claude by default; OpenAI, Gemini, Kimi, or a local Ollama model
optionally) to propose remediation. Fixes are applied only after explicit
approval and only after passing a safety deny-list.
.PP
The tool is FIPS-aware: it relies on the system OpenSSL, pins TLS 1.2+, and uses
SHA-2 digests only. It can export PDF, HTML, JSON, and SARIF 2.1.0 reports, and
ships a systemd timer for unattended scan-and-report.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
These precede the command.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the version and exit.
.TP
.BI \-\-config " CONFIG"
Path to a configuration JSON file.
.TP
.BI \-\-state\-dir " DIR"
Override the state/cache directory (findings and reports).
.TP
.BI \-\-provider " PROVIDER"
AI provider: \fBclaude\fR, \fBopenai\fR, \fBgemini\fR, \fBkimi\fR, or \fBlocal\fR.
.TP
.BI \-\-model " MODEL"
Model id override, e.g. \fIclaude-opus-4-8\fR or \fIllama3.2:1b\fR.
.SH SEVERITY VALUES
Where a severity is accepted, use one of, in increasing order:
.BR low ", " moderate ", " important ", " critical
(\fBhigh\fR is treated as \fBimportant\fR, \fBmedium\fR as \fBmoderate\fR).
.SH COMMANDS
.SS info
Show version, FIPS status, GPU/CPU, available scanners, and AI provider readiness.
No options.
.SS scan
Detect vulnerabilities, enrich from CVE feeds, print a table, and save findings.
.TP
.BI \-\-scanner " NAME"
Scanner to run (repeatable): \fBdnf\fR, \fBoscap\fR, \fBssh\fR, \fBsystemd\fR, \fBports\fR, or \fBwebroot\fR. Use \fB\-\-all\fR to run every available scanner.
.TP
.BI \-\-min\-severity " SEV"
Only keep findings at or above this severity.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-enrich
Skip Red Hat/NVD CVE-feed lookups (faster; fully offline).
.TP
.BI \-\-pdf " PATH"
Also write a PDF report.
.TP
.BI \-\-json " PATH"
Also write a JSON export.
.TP
.BI \-\-sarif " PATH"
Also write a SARIF 2.1.0 file.
.SS fix
Ask the AI provider to propose remediation, then apply with approval. Proposed
commands are screened against a safety deny-list. The per-finding prompt accepts
\fBy\fR (yes), \fBn\fR (no), \fBa\fR (all), or \fBq\fR (quit).
.TP
.B \-\-scan
Scan first instead of using the last saved findings.
.TP
.BI \-\-scanner " NAME"
Scanner(s) to use with \fB\-\-scan\fR (repeatable).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-enrich
Skip CVE-feed enrichment with \fB\-\-scan\fR.
.TP
.BI \-\-min\-severity " SEV"
Only act on findings at or above this severity.
.TP
.B \-\-yes
Auto-approve every screened fix (non-interactive).
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Produce the plan but execute nothing.
.TP
.BI \-\-pdf " PATH"
Write a PDF report after fixing.
.SS report
Render a report or export from the last saved scan. The output extension selects
the format: \fI.pdf\fR, \fI.html\fR, \fI.json\fR, or \fI.sarif\fR.
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIPATH\fR
Output file (default \fIvulnscan-ai-report.pdf\fR).
.TP
.BI \-\-min\-severity " SEV"
Only include findings at or above this severity.
.SS providers
List AI providers, default models, key environment variables, and readiness.
No options.
.SS setup
Interactive first-run wizard: detect GPU/RAM, list offline models sized to the
host, optionally install Ollama, download the chosen model, and save it as the
default provider/model. Offered automatically on the first interactive run;
suppress with \fBVULNSCANAI_NO_SETUP=1\fR. No options.
.SS update\-oval
Detect the distribution and download/stage the OpenSCAP OVAL CVE feed under
\fI<state-dir>/oval/\fR, enabling the \fBoscap\fR scanner. No options.
.SS scheduled
Non-interactive scan and dated report for the systemd timer or cron. Never
applies fixes. Rotates old reports and can signal severity via the exit code.
.TP
.BI \-\-scanner " NAME"
Scanner(s) to run (repeatable).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-enrich
Skip CVE-feed enrichment.
.TP
.BI \-\-min\-severity " SEV"
Only keep findings at or above this severity.
.TP
.B \-\-plan
Embed AI remediation proposals in the report (no execution).
.TP
.B \-\-html
Write an HTML report instead of PDF.
.TP
.BI \-\-keep " N"
Retain only the newest N reports (default 30).
.TP
.BI \-\-fail\-on " SEVERITY"
Exit 3 if any finding is at or above this severity.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
No findings to act on, or a step failed (e.g. OVAL download).
.TP
.B 2
AI provider error (key missing, or model/server unreachable).
.TP
.B 3
\fBscheduled \-\-fail\-on\fR threshold met.
.TP
.B 130
Interrupted.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
API key for the \fBclaude\fR provider (default).
.TP
.BR OPENAI_API_KEY ", " GEMINI_API_KEY ", " MOONSHOT_API_KEY
API keys for \fBopenai\fR, \fBgemini\fR, and \fBkimi\fR respectively.
.TP
.BR OLLAMA_HOST ", " OLLAMA_MODEL ", " OLLAMA_TIMEOUT
Local (\fBlocal\fR) provider: server URL, model name, request timeout (seconds).
.TP
.B NVD_API_KEY
Optional; raises the NVD enrichment rate limit.
.TP
.BR VULNSCANAI_PROVIDER ", " VULNSCANAI_MODEL ", " VULNSCANAI_STATE_DIR
Override the provider, model, and state directory.
.TP
.B VULNSCANAI_NO_SETUP
If set, never run the first-run wizard automatically.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/vulnscan-ai/config.json
System configuration.
.TP
.I ~/.config/vulnscan-ai/config.json
Per-user configuration (where the setup wizard saves its choice).
.TP
.I /var/lib/vulnscan-ai/
State directory: findings.json, reports/, oval/.
.SH "CONFIGURATION PRECEDENCE"
Highest wins: command-line flags, then environment variables, then the per-user
config, then the system config, then built-in defaults.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dnf (8),
.BR oscap (8),
.BR systemctl (1).
Full reference and examples: \fI/usr/share/doc/vulnscan-ai/COMMANDS.md\fR.
